## CRITICAL XHTML Requirements

1. **Document Structure** - MUST include:
   ```xml
   <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
   <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
   <html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
   ```

2. **CSS 2.1 ONLY** - Flying Saucer does NOT support:
   - NO flexbox (display: flex)
   - NO grid (display: grid)
   - NO gap, row-gap, column-gap
   - NO align-items, justify-content, flex-direction
   - NO CSS variables (var(--name))
   - NO rem units on body (use pt, px, in, cm)

3. **Use these instead:**
   - Tables for layout
   - Floats (float: left/right, clear: both)
   - Absolute/relative positioning
   - Standard CSS properties

4. **Tag Rules:**
   - All tags MUST be properly closed
   - Self-closing tags: `<br />`, `<hr />`, `<img ... />`
   - No unclosed tags - every `<tag>` needs `</tag>`
   - Use `&amp;` for &, `&lt;` for <, `&gt;` for >

5. **Images:**
   - Use base64: `<img src="data:image/png;base64,..." />`
   - Or absolute file:// URLs
   - Keep images reasonably sized; do not exceed page height
   - Use `<figure class="image-block">` with `<figcaption>` for captions
   - Do NOT wrap tables and images in the same keep-together container
   - Avoid `keep-together` on any section that includes an image
   - If a section has a table and image, place the table first, then the figure after it

6. **Page Control:**
   - `page-break-before: always;` - force page break
   - `page-break-inside: avoid;` - keep element together
   - `@page` rules for margins/size

